<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet follow<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
I can't believe nobody else uses the follow. That actually makes the pet try and move his sorry butt out of melee range of mob A before he swings at mob B. Using earth pet this macro is well nigh unbeatable since the mobs pretty much stay rooted but, even with say my 62 water pet getting beat on he tags a second mob and grabs aggro. Stick that little extra line in there, you will see the beauty!! <br>
